<span id="freeTextContainer5999681523569098298">Where to begin with this one.....I honestly would never have read this book if I had not had other&apos;s trusted opinions egging me on. I don&apos;t normally read animal books, or books about nature and people in the wild, or extremely wordy novels that go on and on about trees and such. <br/><br/>This book was nothing like any of that. <br/><br/>Instead it was magnificently worded with adjectives I loved (I&apos;m big on adjectives) and the characters had personalities that are even now still in my head. I cheered on Edgar, lov</span>
  <span id="freeText5999681523569098298" style="display:none">Where to begin with this one.....I honestly would never have read this book if I had not had other's trusted opinions egging me on. I don't normally read animal books, or books about nature and people in the wild, or extremely wordy novels that go on and on about trees and such. <br /><br />This book was nothing like any of that. <br /><br />Instead it was magnificently worded with adjectives I loved (I'm big on adjectives) and the characters had personalities that are even now still in my head. I cheered on Edgar, loved Almondine like I love my 16 year old cat, puzzled over Trudy, cried over Gar and even Page, wanted to hang out with Henry, and tried to figure out how bad or how good Claude really was. This book was truly wonderful.<br /><br />Thank you to all of you that pushed me to read it.....I loved every page of it.</span>
